{'@context': 'https://schema.org/', '@type': 'Recipe', 'folder': 'steak_with_tamarind_caramel_and_chimichurri', 'name': 'Steak with Tamarind Caramel and Chimichurri', 'image': ['steak_with_tamarind_caramel_and_chimichurri_0.jpg'], 'author': {'@type': 'Person', 'name': 'Fin'}, 'keywords': 'Steak, Tamarind Caramel, Chimichurri, Beef, Fusion Cuisine, Pan-Seared Steak, Main Course, Gourmet, Homemade Sauce, Spicy, Sweet and Sour, Herbaceous, Garlic, Chili, Parsley, Oregano, Red Wine Vinegar, Steak Dinner, Caramel Sauce Recipe, Argentinian Sauce, Date Night Recipe, Foodie, Cast Iron Steak', 'datePublished': '2025-03-9', 'lastMod': '2025-03-9', 'description': 'A sensational fusion dish featuring a perfectly pan-seared steak served with two powerful condiments: a sweet and tangy tamarind caramel that adds a unique twist, and a fresh, vibrant chimichurri packed with herbs, garlic, and a hint of chili. A truly impressive main course for any occasion.', 'prepTime': 'PT10M', 'cookTime': 'PT20M', 'totalTime': 'PT30M', 'recipeYield': '2 Servings', 'recipeCategory': 'Main Course', 'recipeCuisine': 'Fusion', 'nutrition': {'@type': 'NutritionInformation', 'calories': '1300-1450 calories per serving (estimated)'}, 'recipeIngredient': ['Caramel:', '1/2 cup White Sugar', '40g Unsalted Butter', '4 tbsp Cream', '1 tsp Tamarind Paste', '', 'Chimichurri', '1/2 cup Olive Oil', '2 tbsp Red Wine Vinegar', '1/2 cup Fresh Parsley', '4 cloves Garlic', '2 Birdseye Chilis', '2 tbsp Fresh Oregano', '', 'Other:', '400g+ Steak'], 'ingredientKeywords': ['White Sugar', 'Sugar', 'Unsalted Butter', 'Butter', 'Cream', 'Tamarind Paste', 'Tamarind', 'Olive Oil', 'Red Wine Vinegar', 'Vinegar', 'Fresh Parsley', 'Parsley', 'Garlic', 'Birdseye Chili', 'Chili', 'Fresh Oregano', 'Oregano', 'Steak', 'Beef'], 'equipment': ['Heavy Pan', 'Small Saucepan'], 'recipeInstructions': [{'@type': 'HowToStep', 'text': 'For the chimichurri: Mince the garlic. Finely chop the parsley, oregano and chili. Mix everything together and season with pepper and salt to taste.', 'name': 'Prep chimichurri', 'url': 1}, {'@type': 'HowToStep', 'text': 'For the caramel: Heat sugar in a small saucepan over low heat. Whisk frequently. Eventually it will start to clump and then melt.', 'name': 'Start caramel', 'url': 2}, {'@type': 'HowToStep', 'text': 'Once sugar is fully melted take it off the heat and whisk in the butter. This should sizzle and thats fine.', 'name': 'Add butter to caramel', 'url': 3}, {'@type': 'HowToStep', 'text': 'Now add cream and tamarind. Whisk through until combined fully. Let it cool.', 'name': 'Add cream and tamarind to caramel', 'url': 4}, {'@type': 'HowToStep', 'text': "Heat a heavy pan, ideally a cast iron, with a bit of oil until it's just smoking. Cook steak about 2m either side or to your liking. Enjoy with the condiments!", 'name': 'Cook steak', 'url': 5}], 'notes': ['If you make the condiments in advance, you can just whip them out of the fridge/freezer and sear the steak for a quick dinner.', 'I like this with a bit of extra tamarind in the caramel for a zingier flavour.']}